                    <img src="~/assets/img/avukat-emin-oz-modal.jpg" class="modal-bio-img img-fluid" alt="Person 1 Photo">
                    <p class="bio-content">
                        Renowned attorney Emin Öz, founder of Öz & Partners, was born in 1950 in Silifke, Mersin. Graduating from Istanbul University Faculty of Law in 1973, he established his own office in Mersin in 1974, starting his career as a lawyer.
                        Emin Öz, who took on the role of attorney in numerous political cases before and after the military coup on September 12, 1980, was one of the lawyers defending Alparslan Türkeş after the coup.
                    </p>
                    <p class="bio-content">
                        In 1989, he was elected as a member of the Mersin Provincial General Assembly. While serving in this position, he was elected as the Mersin Provincial Chairman of the Motherland Party in 1993 and served for 3 terms until 1999. In the 1999 general elections, he ran as an independent candidate from Mersin and demonstrated significant political influence by receiving a high number of votes.
                    </p>
                    <p class="bio-content">
                        In the following years, Emin Öz served in the Central Decision and Administration Board (MKYK) of the Motherland Party for 2 terms. Involved in the economic and commercial world since the early years of his professional life, Attorney Emin Öz served as the chairman of the board of directors of many influential companies, including MESBAŞ (the company operating Mersin Free Zone) and MERTAŞ (a company jointly established by professional chambers and NGOs such as MTSO, MESİAD, and Mersin Chamber of Commerce), shaping Mersin's economic and commercial life. He served as the deputy chairman of the consultation board of MESİAD (Mersin Industrialists and Businessmen Association). He also served on the board of directors of the Mersin Bar Association.
                    </p>
                    <p class="bio-content">
                        Emin Öz also taught law courses at Mersin University Faculty of Maritime and Trade. Approaching the 50th year of his professional career, Attorney Emin Öz is proficient in English and French.
                    </p>
